summary: This is an internal FBI email chain from July 10, 2019, discussing the potential need to execute a search warrant at Jeffrey Epstein's residence for digital media and computer equipment. The email indicates that most of the FBI squad is in Florida interviewing victims, requiring assistance from other squads.

keyFacts: The FBI was planning to execute a search warrant at Jeffrey Epstein's residence for digital media and computer equipment on or around July 11, 2019.
Most of the FBI's Squad C-20 (Crimes Against Children/Human Trafficking) was in Florida interviewing victims at the time, creating a need for additional personnel.
The email chain shows internal FBI coordination regarding resource allocation for the Epstein investigation in July 2019.
